data.title: PyMF: Matched filtering techniques for astronomical images
data.name: pymf
data.description: A python implementation of several matched filtering techniques for astronomical images.

evidence: “PyMF is a pure-Python implementation of several matched filtering image processing techniques. These methods are designed for applications in astronomy…” (indicates a domain-specific analysis tool used in research).
“Please cite Erler, Ramos-Ceja, Basu & Bertoldi (2018) … if you find this code useful in your research.” (shows direct use in producing research results).
Badges and links only reference the GitHub repository and ReadTheDocs documentation; no mention of package managers or binaries, implying distribution via the source repository.
